I had the pleasure of having dinner at a nearby restaurant, where I live in Williamsburg, Brooklyn NY., named Frost Italian Restaurant specializing in seafood. I ordered the baked clams (8) per order, was so delicious, just loved the breading, seasoned well. I ordered chicken cutlet parmigiana with linguine.was good, but not as great as past dishes of this. I must admit,you get a huge portion of this, well worth the price.... For dessert I ordered a cannoli and a cup of cappuccino, the cannoli was delicious, but the cappuccino was so disappointing, was served in a tall glass mug, had no flavor,was watered down... would have been better, if it was served in a cup, with lots of whipped cream and with a cinnamon stick, as I have had it served in other Italian restaurants or while I ordered it in Germany, as I lived there for five years. All in all, I highly recommend this restaurant, but I strongly    suggest getting regular coffee to go with your dessert, as opposed to a cappuccino.....

The food took me back to my childhood of remembering how real Italian food tasted. This was not a restaurant but an experience. The food was all old time recipes that go back decades and decades. You have to try this once and I promise you will love it like we did. Great food.
